swMacBasedAuthState.name: swMacBasedAuthState
swMacBasedAuthState.description: This object enables or disables the MAC-based Access Control status of the device.

swMacBasedAuthMethod.name: swMacBasedAuthMethod
swMacBasedAuthMethod.description: This object indicates the type of authentication method. The RADIUS method is authenticated per authentication server.

swMacBasedAuthPWD.name: swMacBasedAuthPWD
swMacBasedAuthPWD.description: This object indicates the password of the RADIUS authentication method.

swMacBasedAuthVlanName.name: swMacBasedAuthVlanName
swMacBasedAuthVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the MAC-based Access Control guest VLAN.

swMacBasedAuthMemberPorts.name: swMacBasedAuthMemberPorts
swMacBasedAuthMemberPorts.description: This object indicates the member ports of the MAC-based Access Control guest VLAN.

swMacBasedAuthVlanNameDelState.name: swMacBasedAuthVlanNameDelState
swMacBasedAuthVlanNameDelState.description: Used to delete the guest VLAN of MAC-based Access Control.

swMacBasedAuthClearAllAction.name: swMacBasedAuthClearAllAction
swMacBasedAuthClearAllAction.description: Used to clear the authentication state of all the ports.

swMacBasedAuthMaxUser.name: swMacBasedAuthMaxUser
swMacBasedAuthMaxUser.description: This object indicates the maximum number of authorized client(s) on the whole device. Note: The maximum number of the authorized client(s) range is (0..N). The value N means the maximum number. This is determined by the project itself. When 0 is set, the maximum number of authorized clients is unlimited.

swMacBasedAuthFailOver.name: swMacBasedAuthFailOver
swMacBasedAuthFailOver.description: This object sets the RADIUS authentication failover state. When the authentication failover is disabled and the RADIUS servers are unreachable, the authentication will fail. When the authentication failover is enabled and the RADIUS servers authentication are unreachable, the local database will be used to do the authentication. By default, the state is disabled.

swMacBasedAuthRadiusAuthorization.name: swMacBasedAuthRadiusAuthorization
swMacBasedAuthRadiusAuthorization.description: This object sets the acceptance state of RADIUS authorization. When the authorization is enabled for the MAC-based Access Control's RADIUS method, the authorized attributes (for example VLAN, 802.1p default priority, and ACL) assigned by the local database will be accepted if the global authorization state is enabled.

swMacBasedAuthLocalAuthorization.name: swMacBasedAuthLocalAuthorization
swMacBasedAuthLocalAuthorization.description: This object sets the acceptance state of local authorization. When the authorization is enabled for the MAC-based Access Control's local method, the authorized attributes assigned by the local database will be accepted if the global authorization state is enabled.

swMacBasedAuthTrapState.name: swMacBasedAuthTrapState
swMacBasedAuthTrapState.description: This object is used to enable or disable the sending of MAC-based Access Control traps.

swMacBasedAuthLogState.name: swMacBasedAuthLogState
swMacBasedAuthLogState.description: This object is used to enable or disable the generating of MAC-based Access Control logs.

swMacBasedAuthPwdType.name: swMacBasedAuthPwdType
swMacBasedAuthPwdType.description: This object is used to configure the type of RADIUS authentication password for MAC-based Access Control. manual_string: Use the same string as password for all clients do RADIUS authentication, the string can be configured by swMacBasedAuthPWD. client_mac_address: Use the clients MAC address as the password for RADIUS authentication.

swMacBasedAuthPortInfoTable.name: swMacBasedAuthPortInfoTable
swMacBasedAuthPortInfoTable.description: A table that displays the authentication state of every port.

swMacBasedAuthPortInfoEntry.name: swMacBasedAuthPortInfoEntry
swMacBasedAuthPortInfoEntry.description: A table that displays the authentication state for each port.

swMacBasedAuthInfoPortIndex.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoPortIndex
swMacBasedAuthInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the authenticated port number.

swMacBasedAuthInfoMacIndex.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoMacIndex
swMacBasedAuthInfoMacIndex.description: This object indicates the authenticated MAC address.

swMacBasedAuthInfoStatus.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoStatus
swMacBasedAuthInfoStatus.description: This object indicates the authenticated status.

swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVLANName.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVLANName
swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVLANName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name that the port is assigned with once MAC authentication was successful.

swMacBasedAuthClearMacAction.name: swMacBasedAuthClearMacAction
swMacBasedAuthClearMacAction.description: When set to start (2), the user will return to an un-authenticated state. All the timers associated with the user will be reset. When the administrator performs a get operation, it always returns the other (1).

swMacBasedAuthInfoPriority.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoPriority
swMacBasedAuthInfoPriority.description: This object indicates the priority that the port or MAC address is assigned to after it passes authentication. -1 will be displayed when the port or MAC address has not been assigned any priority

swMacBasedAuthInfoAgingTime.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoAgingTime
swMacBasedAuthInfoAgingTime.description: This object indicates the remaining time until the authenticated client returns to an unauthenticated state. -1 will be displayed before the port or MAC address passes authentication. 0 will be displayed when the aging time is set to infinite on the port. -2 indicates the host aging timeout, but MAC-based Access Control will hold this entry as expired (for stacking performance) and after the time has expired, the switch will delete it.

swMacBasedAuthInfoBlockTime.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoBlockTime
swMacBasedAuthInfoBlockTime.description: This object indicates the remaining time until the authentication failure client is allowed to start a new authentication. -1 will be displayed after the port or MAC address passes authentication. -2 indicates the host block timeout, but MAC-based Access Control will hold this entry as expired (for stacking performance) and after the time has expired, the switch will delete it.

swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVID.name: swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVID
swMacBasedAuthInfoAssignVID.description: This object indicates the VID that the port is assigned to once the MAC authentication was successful.

swMacBasedAuthStateTable.name: swMacBasedAuthStateTable
swMacBasedAuthStateTable.description: This table contains the MAC-based Access Control clients' authentication information.

swMacBasedAuthStateEntry.name: swMacBasedAuthStateEntry
swMacBasedAuthStateEntry.description: This list contains the MAC-based Access Control host's authentication information.

swMacBasedAuthStatePort.name: swMacBasedAuthStatePort
swMacBasedAuthStatePort.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's port number.

swMacBasedAuthStateOriginalVID.name: swMacBasedAuthStateOriginalVID
swMacBasedAuthStateOriginalVID.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's original received VLAN ID.

swMacBasedAuthStateMacAddr.name: swMacBasedAuthStateMacAddr
swMacBasedAuthStateMacAddr.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's MAC address.

swMacBasedAuthStateAuthStatus.name: swMacBasedAuthStateAuthStatus
swMacBasedAuthStateAuthStatus.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's authentication state.

swMacBasedAuthStateAssignVID.name: swMacBasedAuthStateAssignVID
swMacBasedAuthStateAssignVID.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's assign VLAN ID.

swMacBasedAuthStateAssignPriority.name: swMacBasedAuthStateAssignPriority
swMacBasedAuthStateAssignPriority.description: Specifies the MAC-based Access Control host's priority assigned when it passes authentication. -1 indicates the host has no priority assigned.

swMacBasedAuthStateRemainTime.name: swMacBasedAuthStateRemainTime
swMacBasedAuthStateRemainTime.description: Specifies the remaining MAC-based Access Control host's aging or block time. When host's authentication state is 'authenticated' in swMacBasedAuthStateAuthStatus, this object indicates the host's aging time, the units are in minutes. When host's authentication state is 'blocked' in swMacBasedAuthStateAuthStatus, this object indicates the host's block time, the units are in seconds. 0 indicates that the authenticated host on the port will never age out. -2 indicates the host aging or block timeout, but MAC-based Access Control will hold this entry as expired (for stacking performance) and after the time expired, the switch will delete it.

swMacBasedAuthStateDelAction.name: swMacBasedAuthStateDelAction
swMacBasedAuthStateDelAction.description: Used to delete the specified authentication entry. Setting start (2) will delete this MAC-based Access Control host entry.

swMacBasedAuthPortTable.name: swMacBasedAuthPortTable
swMacBasedAuthPortTable.description: A table that contains the method and state for every port.

swMacBasedAuthPortEntry.name: swMacBasedAuthPortEntry
swMacBasedAuthPortEntry.description: A list of method types and states for each port.

swMacBasedAuthPortIndex.name: swMacBasedAuthPortIndex
swMacBasedAuthPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.

swMacBasedAuthPortState.name: swMacBasedAuthPortState
swMacBasedAuthPortState.description: This object enables or disables the authentication state of this port.

swMacBasedAuthPortMode.name: swMacBasedAuthPortMode
swMacBasedAuthPortMode.description: This object specifies the mode of this entry. port_based: All users connected to a port share the first authentication result. host_based: Each user can have its own authentication result.

swMacBasedAuthPortAgingTime.name: swMacBasedAuthPortAgingTime
swMacBasedAuthPortAgingTime.description: Specifies the time period that an authenticated host will be kept in an authenticated state. When the aging time has timed out, the host will be moved back to an unauthenticated state. Note: When 0 is set on the specified port, it means that the aging has been disabled, meaning that the aging time is set to infinite.

swMacBasedAuthPortBlockTime.name: swMacBasedAuthPortBlockTime
swMacBasedAuthPortBlockTime.description: If a host fails to authenticate, the next authentication will not start within the block time unless the user clears the entry state manually. Note: When 0 is set on the specified port, it means that the block authentication fail MAC address block time is set to infinite.

swMacBasedAuthClearPortAction.name: swMacBasedAuthClearPortAction
swMacBasedAuthClearPortAction.description: When set to start (2), the specified port will return to an un-authenticated state. All the timers associated with the specified port will be reset. When the administrator performs a get operation, it always returns the other (1).

swMacBasedAuthPortMaxUser.name: swMacBasedAuthPortMaxUser
swMacBasedAuthPortMaxUser.description: This object indicates the maximum number of authorized client(s) on the specified port. Note: The maximum number of authorized client (s) range is (0..N). The value N means the maximum number is determined by the project itself. When 0 is set on the specified port, the maximum number of authorized client(s) has no limit.

swMacBasedAuthDatabaseTable.name: swMacBasedAuthDatabaseTable
swMacBasedAuthDatabaseTable.description: A table that contains the MAC-based Access Control account information.

swMacBasedAuthDatabaseEntry.name: swMacBasedAuthDatabaseEntry
swMacBasedAuthDatabaseEntry.description: A list that contains the MAC-based Access Control account information.

swMacBasedAuthDatabaseMacIndex.name: swMacBasedAuthDatabaseMacIndex
swMacBasedAuthDatabaseMacIndex.description: This object indicates the MAC address for this user account.

swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVlanName.name: swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVlanName
swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name for this user account.

swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVID.name: swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVID
swMacBasedAuthDatabaseVID.description: This object indicates the VID for this user account. 0 indicates to delete the configured VID in this user account.

swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedSuccess.name: swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedSuccess
swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedSuccess.description: The trap is sent when a MAC-based Access Control host has successfully logged in.

swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedFail.name: swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedFail
swMacBasedAccessControlLoggedFail.description: The trap is sent when a MAC-based Access Control host's login fails.

swMacBasedAccessControlAgesOut.name: swMacBasedAccessControlAgesOut
swMacBasedAccessControlAgesOut.description: The trap is sent when a MAC-based Access Control host ages out.

swMacBasedAuthVID.name: swMacBasedAuthVID
swMacBasedAuthVID.description: The VLAN ID for the host already exists.
